<br>
I've played quite a bit with my Mage/Necro combo, as well as my Shammie/SK.  I have a bit more trouble playing the Nec/Tank, tanks do a lot more work then most people give them credit for, and between pet/root/ST/Dot, Necros can stay pretty busy as well.  Two Casters are much easier because most things can be hotkeyed, even with two pets.  I see a lot of Cleric/War combos, and generally speaking I find people tend to die more or at least come closer to it, again because you can't hotkey your movements, bash and taunt recycle faster then most spells, etc., so while the Tank is busy the Cleric is unavailable.  Personally I wouldn't want to dual with a Cleric or Enchanter as one of them, because frankly they stay pretty busy in raid type situations, if you're in a strong group in Seb it might be different.  As someone who duals, I hate it when I see someone dualling and their tank is always either the last one in the fight, or because their other pays so much attention to HIS needs that the rest of the group can suffer.<br>
